{"x": "polish the paper bellow.\n \n  \\caption{Comparison between the traditional pretraining-finetuning paradigm and our proposed framework GUR: instead of domain-adaptive further-pretraining with only LM objective and finetuning on various downstream tasks, we post-pretrain the model with LM and CL objectives on custom domain and zero-shot for NLU, NLG, and recall tasks. The model \"GUR-CL\" is pre-trained in the traditional approach without CL objective. The other models are pre-trained in the second approach. Without extra resources, the model \"GUR-FULL\" keeps the same LM ability as the model by the traditional approach and gains the ability of text representation in our approach. The models are initialized from a pretrained LM on a general corpus at the least cost.}", "y_w": "You are an academic editor.\n\nOBJECTIVE:\nImprove the clarity and professionalism of an academic caption.\n\nINPUT:\nUse the provided caption text.\n\nOUTPUT:\nReturn a polished version.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\nPreserve original meaning.", "y_l": "Improve the provided academic paper caption."}
