{"x": "GIve me a sample code to use LIN protocol in Raspberry pi in python", "y_w": "You are an embedded systems engineer.\n\nTASK:\nProvide sample Python code for using the LIN protocol with a Raspberry Pi.\n\nLANGUAGE:\nPython\n\nINPUTS:\nAssume a Raspberry Pi is connected to a compatible LIN transceiver or UART-to-LIN interface.\n\nOUTPUTS:\nProvide setup requirements, wiring assumptions, sample Python code, and a brief explanation of how the code sends and receives LIN frames.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\nKeep the code practical, readable, and suitable for basic LIN communication testing.", "y_l": "Provide a Python example for using the LIN (Local Interconnect Network) protocol on a Raspberry Pi."}
{"x": "Given a corpus of text, extract all the sentences with a subject-verb-object structure and replace all the nouns in each sentence with their corresponding synonyms from a pre-defined synonym database. For instance, consider the following sentence: \"John drove to the store to buy milk.\" Here, the noun \"John\" can be replaced with \"Jonathan,\" \"the store\" can be replaced with \"the market,\" and \"milk\" can be replaced with \"dairy products.\" Apply this transformation to generate a new sentence that still maintains the original meaning but with a different lexical representation. In addition, provide a table that lists the original and the corresponding synonyms used for each noun. Finally, write a Python code to implement this sentence transformation algorithm.", "y_w": "You are a Python NLP developer.\n\nTASK:\nWrite a Python program that processes a text corpus, identifies sentences with a subject-verb-object structure, replaces nouns with synonyms from a predefined synonym database, and outputs the transformed sentences.\n\nLANGUAGE:\nPython\n\nINPUTS:\n\nA text corpus\nA predefined synonym database mapping nouns to synonyms\n\nOUTPUTS:\n\nExtracted SVO sentences\nTransformed sentences with noun replacements\nA table listing each original noun and its replacement synonym\nPython implementation code\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n\nPreserve the original meaning as much as possible\nOnly replace nouns found in the synonym database\nKeep the code readable and well-structured", "y_l": "Create a Python program that processes a text corpus by identifying sentences with a subject-verb-object (SVO) structure and replacing nouns with synonyms from a predefined synonym database."}
{"x": "How can I retrieve information on the state of California using Python code? Can you provide a sample code that utilizes web scraping to gather data from reliable sources such as government websites or reputable news outlets?", "y_w": "You are a Python web scraping developer.\n\nTASK:\nWrite sample Python code to retrieve reliable information about the state of California using web scraping.\n\nLANGUAGE:\nPython\n\nINPUTS:\nUse reliable public sources such as government websites or reputable news outlets.\n\nOUTPUTS:\nProvide:\n\nRecommended source types\nPython scraping code\nData extraction logic\nExample output format\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n\nUse ethical scraping practices\nRespect website terms and robots.txt\nPrefer official or reputable sources\nKeep the code beginner-friendly", "y_l": "Write Python code that retrieves information about the state of California using web scraping."}
{"x": "You are given a code snippet that represents a function in a programming language. The function takes no arguments and returns a boolean value. Your task is to identify the problem in the code snippet and modify it to fix the issue.", "y_w": "You are a software debugging assistant.\n\nTASK:\nAnalyze the provided code snippet for a function that takes no arguments and returns a boolean value. Identify the issue and modify the code to fix it.\n\nLANGUAGE:\nUse the programming language of the provided code snippet.\n\nINPUTS:\nA code snippet containing the faulty function.\n\nOUTPUTS:\nProvide:\n\nThe identified problem\nThe corrected code\nA brief explanation of the fix\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n\nDo not rewrite unrelated code\nKeep the fix minimal\nPreserve the intended behavior", "y_l": "Analyze the provided code snippet for a function that takes no arguments and returns a boolean value."}
