{"x": "write json file in python", "y_w": "You are a Python programming tutor.\n\nTASK:\nShow how to write data to a JSON file in Python.\n\nLANGUAGE:\nPython\n\nINPUTS:\nUse a sample dictionary or list as the data source.\n\nOUTPUTS:\nProvide:\n\nSimple Python code\nExample JSON output\nBrief explanation of the main steps\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n\nUse Python’s built-in json module\nKeep the example beginner-friendly", "y_l": "Write Python code that saves data to a JSON file."}
{"x": "You are given a code snippet that defines an interface named `IRunnable` with a single method `Run`. The `Run` method takes two parameters: a `Node` object named `root` and an `IDiagnostics` object named `diagnostics`. Your task is to implement a class that implements the `IRunnable` interface and provides a concrete implementation of the `Run` method.\n \n The `Node` class represents a node in a data structure and has not been defined in the given code snippet. You need to define the `Node` class yourself. The `IDiagnostics` class represents a diagnostics service and has also not been defined in the given code snippet. You do not need to define the `IDiagnostics` class, as it will be provided to you during testing.\n \n Your implementation should adhere to the following specifications:\n - The `Run` method should be void and should not return any value.\n - The `Run` method should take the `root` node as input and perform some operations on it according to the problem requirements.\n - The `diagnostics` object should be used to log any diagnostic messages during the execution of the `Run` method. You should use the `Log` method provided by the `diagnostics` object to log the messages. The `Log` method takes a single string parameter representing the message to be logged.\n \n Write a class that implements the `IRunnable` interface and provides a concrete implementation of the `Run` method to solve the problem at hand.", "y_w": "You are a software developer implementing an interface-based class.\n\nTASK:\nImplement a class that satisfies the IRunnable interface and provides a concrete Run method.\n\nLANGUAGE:\nUse the language implied by the provided interface code.\n\nINPUTS:\n\nInterface: IRunnable\nMethod: Run(Node root, IDiagnostics diagnostics)\nIDiagnostics is provided during testing\nDefine a basic Node class if needed\n\nOUTPUTS:\nProvide the complete class implementation, including the Run method.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n\nRun must return void\nUse diagnostics.Log(string message) for diagnostic output\nDo not define IDiagnostics if it is provided externally\nKeep implementation minimal and testable", "y_l": "Implement a C# class that conforms to an existing IRunnable interface."}
{"x": "laravel markdown different message template and layout", "y_w": "You are a Laravel developer.\n\nTASK:\nExplain how to use different Markdown mail message templates and layouts in Laravel.\n\nLANGUAGE / FRAMEWORK:\nLaravel / PHP\n\nINPUTS:\nAssume the project uses Laravel Mailables with Markdown email templates.\n\nOUTPUTS:\nProvide:\n\nFolder structure\nExample Mailable class\nExample Markdown template\nExample custom layout\nExplanation of how to select different templates\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n\nUse Laravel conventions\nKeep examples practical\nAvoid unrelated email configuration details", "y_l": "Create a guide for using different Markdown email templates and layouts in Laravel."}
