{"x": "Write code for a react component for a checkbox which toggles on the three states: true, false and indeterminate.", "y_w": "You are a React frontend developer.\n\nTASK:\nWrite a React component for a tri-state checkbox that toggles between true, false, and indeterminate.\n\nLANGUAGE / FRAMEWORK:\nReact with JavaScript or TypeScript.\n\nINPUTS:\nThe component should manage its own state unless props are specified.\n\nOUTPUTS:\nProvide:\n\nComplete component code\nState transition logic\nBasic usage example\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n\nUse accessible checkbox behavior\nKeep the component reusable\nAvoid unnecessary dependencies", "y_l": "Write a React component for a tri-state checkbox that cycles through three values: true, false, and indeterminate."}
